metrics_conclusion: In terms of chords and melody, The Girl has complexity on par with the typical song, having near-average scores in Melodic Complexity and Chord-Bass Melody and below-average scores in Chord Complexity, Chord-Melody Tension and Chord Progression Novelty.

metadata.editComments: I just learned in Music Theory that V/x can sometimes resolve deceptively at a cadence the same way V (of I) can sometimes resolve to something other than one. One of the most common deceptive resolutions is V to vi (or VI in minor). That means V/vi to IV actually makes sense because it is essentially V/vi going to VI/vi.
